Relicensed verify-only source (authorized)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The two verify cores and their carrier types were extracted from the
Open Agentic Platform (OAP), where they carry SPDX headers reading
`AGPL-3.0-or-later`. Relicensing this extracted, verify-only source to
Apache-2.0 is the prerogative of the sole copyright holder (Bartek Kus) and is
an explicit, authorized act (OAP spec 219-tenant-tail-verifier-toolkit; the
tenant-tail handoff). The extraction is verify-only by construction: the
identity-bearing emitter (the certificate builder, signing-key handling,
`build-certificate`) is excluded and never ported.

Extraction map (OAP source -> tenant-tail destination):

  crates/factory-engine/src/governance_certificate.rs
      -> crates/tenant-tail-core/src/certificate.rs
         (verify path only; builder/signing/generation stripped; the lone
          spec-spine seam `validate_spec_id_resolution` is feature-gated OFF
          and links no spec-spine crate in the vended build)

  crates/factory-engine/src/inter_stage_manifest.rs
      -> crates/tenant-tail-core/src/inter_stage_manifest.rs
         (types + `verify_manifest`; key-minting / signing / session stripped)

  crates/factory-engine/src/platform_jws.rs
      -> crates/tenant-tail-core/src/platform_jws.rs
         (compact-JWS verification; verify-only as authored)

  crates/provenance-validator/  (already a standalone crate)
      -> crates/tenant-tail-core/src/provenance/
         (the pure `validate()` and read-only `audit()` pipeline)

  crates/factory-contracts/src/{provenance,knowledge,budget}.rs
      -> crates/tenant-tail-types/src/{provenance,knowledge,budget}.rs
         (the bounded carrier slice the validator consumes; the heavier
          factory-contracts modules and the agent-frontmatter / ts-rs leaf are
          deliberately left behind)

Per the relicense, OAP's per-file AGPL SPDX header lines are NOT carried into
the ported files; matching spec-spine's convention, the ported files carry no
per-file SPDX header.
